    "caption": "Black, white, and shot through with iridescent green — and extremely curious.",
    "shortDescription": "Magpies are one of the few non-mammal animals that recognize themselves in a mirror — they look at their reflection, touch a mark placed on their own body, and understand what they're seeing. They're chatty, bold, and love to investigate anything shiny or unusual. Fun fact: Magpies build domed nests with a mud bowl inside and a thorny roof of sticks to keep predators out."
